INSERT INTO "bars" VALUES(1,'Joaquin “Waah” Dean Talks The Rise Of Ruff Ryders On ‘The Combat Jack Show’','<p><a href="http://okp-cdn.okayplayer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/combat-jack-show-lead-alt.jpg"><img src="http://okp-cdn.okayplayer.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/combat-jack-show-lead-alt.jpg" alt="combat-jack-show-lead-alt" width="640" height="640" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-68136" /></a></p>
<p><strong><a href="http://www.ruffryders.com/" target="_blank">Ruff Ryders Entertainment</a></strong> co-founder <strong><a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/zackomalleygreenburg/2010/10/06/swizz-beatz-uncle-relaunching-ruff-ryders-with-unorthodox-business-plan-dmx-to-return-jadakiss-alicia-keys-eve/" target="_blank">Joaquin &#8220;Waah&#8221; Dean</a></strong> takes the hot seat in the latest episode of <em><a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/news/big-krit-combat-jack-show-cadillactica-interview-mp3.html">The Combat Jack Show</a></em> to drop a bit of hip-hop history, beginning with his early days in the Bronx living in the apartment above <strong><a href="http://djkoolherc.com/" target="_blank">Kool Herc</a></strong> to teaming with his brother <strong><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruff_Ryders_Entertainment" target="_blank">Darrin &#8220;Dee&#8221; Dean</a></strong> to shake the flossed-out foundations of late-90&#8217;s hip-hop with the unmistakably rugged Ruff Ryders sound led by a breakout artist named <strong><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4FFK5Oh10os" target="_blank">DMX</a></strong>.  <strong><a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/news/common-big-sean-diamonds-combat-jack-show-mp3.html">Combat Jack</a></strong> primes your ears for the latest with a brief rundown of the label&#8217;s impressive resume:</p>
<blockquote><p>You think you know the scope of the Ruff Ryders history? You heard all the stories about DMX, Eve, &#8220;The L.O.X.&#8221; Swizz Beats and the Def Jam takeover? Co-founder Joaquin &#8220;Waah&#8221; Dean takes the history back to the ground zero of Hip Hop with Kool Herc, to the legendary DMX vs Jay Z battle, to taking over the history and more. No shiny suits will be worn during the listening of this episode. Nothing but #BlockWork here b.</p></blockquote>
<p>Check the track below to listen to the full interview with Joaquin &#8220;Waah&#8221; Dean.  Stay tuned for more from <em>The Combat Jack Show</em>.</p>
