INSERT INTO "bars" VALUES(5,'DJ Premier & Royce Da 5’9″ Unleash The Fierce Title-Track Of Their Forthcoming ‘PRhyme’ LP','<p><a href="http://okp-cdn.okayplayer.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/royce-da-59-dj-premier-prhyme.jpeg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-81088" src="http://okp-cdn.okayplayer.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/royce-da-59-dj-premier-prhyme.jpeg" alt="DJ Premier &amp; Royce Da 5''9&quot; Unleash The Title-Track Of Their Forthcoming ''PRhyme'' LP " width="715" height="715" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/dj-premier"><strong> DJ Premier</strong> </a>and <a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/royce-da-59"><strong>Royce Da 5&#8217;9&#8243;</strong></a> have been teasing us with morsels from their upcoming collaborative <em>project PRhyme </em>for a minute now. Today they&#8217;ve unveiled a fierce new offering from the album with its title-track, helmed by the supreme beat constructing wizardry of <a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/adrian-younge"><strong>Adrian Younge</strong></a>. &#8220;PRhyme&#8221; finds the Slaughterhouse MC going schizo, playing (at least) two sides of a dastardly dialogue, making a damn good case for him being in his prime. It&#8217;s the third drop from what is shaping up to be one of the most anticipated records of the year with the soul-selector Younge at its core, which was made even more clear in the clip for <a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/news/dj-premier-royce-da-5-9-prhyme-u-looz-video.html">&#8220;U Looz,&#8221;</a> with the fellas posting up in AY&#8217;s record shop to deliver that true-school heat. If you&#8217;ve yet to experience the dopeness of this project, I encourage you to jump back and get familiar. And if you have had the sense to put your ears to what Preemo and Royce have been cooking up, then go ahead and preorder the record on <a href="http://bit.ly/1tfZVro" target="_blank">iTunes</a> today ahead of its December 9th release. Stream the title-track to the forthcoming collaborative LP from Royce Da 5&#8217;9&#8243; and DJ Premier below and keep it locked for all things <em>PRhyme.</em></p>
