<p>It&#8217;s that time of the year again, folks. Okayplayer is proud to announce that we&#8217;ll be taking over <a href="http://www.brooklynbowl.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Brooklyn Bowl</strong></a> for another proper holiday warm-up on December 11th with OKP&#8217;s favorite soul-searing musical madman <a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/bilal%20"><strong>Bilal</strong></a>, Brooklyn&#8217;s own <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dragons_of_Zynth" target="_blank"><strong>Dragons Of Zynth</strong></a> and best-kept-secret of the Golden Age legend <a href="http://www.discogs.com/artist/101845-Rashad-Smith?type=Credits&amp;subtype=Production" target="_blank"><strong>Rashad &#8220;Tumbling Dice&#8221; Smith</strong></a> bringing you heat on the ones and twos, produced by <strong><a href="http://www.jillnewmanproductions.com/" target="_blank">Jill Newman Productions</a></strong>. But the funk won&#8217;t stop there, as <a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/questlove%20" target="_blank"><strong>Questlove</strong></a> will be taking the baton with another masterful Bowl Train set, the only proper way to tie off any Thursday night in Brooklyn. So come one, come all. Bring your father, your mother, your sister and your brother over to Brooklyn Bowl Thursday December 11th for an evening of funky frequencies and sonic seduction with Bilal, Rashad Smith, Dragons Of Zynth (&#8230;and maybe even a few special guests if we&#8217;re lucky) then have a nightcap with DJ Questo, king of the throwback. Hit the links below to grab your tickets and so promptly. This one&#8217;s a sure-shot sell-out.</p>
