INSERT INTO "bars" VALUES(9,'Ghostface Killah Drops “Love Don’t Live Here No More” + Announces New Concept LP ‘ 36 Seasons’','<p><a href="http://okp-cdn.okayplayer.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/ghostface-killah-love-dont-live-here-no-more-mp3-36-seasons-lp-main.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-81099" src="http://okp-cdn.okayplayer.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/ghostface-killah-love-dont-live-here-no-more-mp3-36-seasons-lp-main.jpg" alt="http://pitchfork.com/news/57400-ghostface-killah-announces-new-album-36-seasons-shares-love-dont-live-here-no-more/" width="715" height="1060" /></a></p>
<p>Take heed, Wu disciples. <a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/ghostface-killah"><strong>Ghostface Killah</strong></a> just dropped a bomb on the world, announcing yet another GFK project will arrive this year in the form of the concept piece <em>36 Seasons</em>. In it Ghostface will take the form of a sonic superhero &#8220;inspired by a quest for personal retribution and bent on saving his community from the grips of crooked authority and urban decay.&#8221; And who better to do so than the mighty Tony Starks; Iron Man in the flesh. The first offering from the album comes in the form of the soulful number &#8220;Love Don&#8217;t Live Here No More,&#8221; featuring the soaring vocal stylings of Blue Note Records&#8217; r&amp;bstress <strong><a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/kandace-springs">Kandace Springs</a> </strong>on the hook. The album will be hitting stores December 9th complete with 20-page booklet of illustrations by various comic artists, just a week after the entirety of <a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/wu-tang-clan"><strong>The Wu-Tang Clan</strong></a> comes storming back on the release of their <em>A Better Tomorrow </em>LP, which will prominently feature ole cocaine biceps. But that isn&#8217;t all the Shaolin mic-slayer&#8217;s got on the way, as he&#8217;ll be dropping the collaborative LP <em>Sour Soul</em> with Canadian punk-funkateers <strong><a href="http://www.okayplayer.com/tag/badbadnotgood">BADBADNOTGOOD</a> </strong>on February 17th. So there&#8217;s a whole lot of loving heading our way. You ready? Stream the lead-off single &#8220;Love Don&#8217;t Live Here No More&#8221; down below and preorder <em>36 Seasons</em> on <a href="http://bit.ly/10RhPW5" target="_blank">iTunes</a> today.</p>
